2 \cos^{-1}x =2 \sin^{-1}x
 \cos^{-1}x = \sin^{-1}x
\arccos x
\in[0,\pi]
\implies 2\arccos x
\in[0,2\pi]
\arcsin x
\in[-\frac\pi2,\frac\pi2]
[0,\frac\pi2]
\sin^{-1}(2x \sqrt {1-x^2})=2\arccos x
0\le 2\arccos x\le \frac\pi2\iff 0\le \arccos x\le\frac\pi4\iff 1\ge x\ge\cos\frac\pi4=\frac1{\sqrt2} 
2\cos^{-1}(x)=\sin^{-1}\Big(2x\sqrt{1 - x^2}\Big)
